documentation.text: @dev Only used for collateral currency liquidation

calculateCollateralCurrencyLiquidation(a.notice: Calculates local and collateral currency transfers for a liquidation. This is a stateful method because it may settle the liquidated account if required. However, it can be called using staticcall off chain to determine the net currency amounts required before liquidating.

params.maxCollateralLiquidation: maximum amount of collateral (inclusive of cash and nTokens) to liquidate
params.maxNTokenLiquidation: maximum amount of nTokens to purchase (if any)

returns._1: collateral asset cash paid to liquidator (positive)

calculateLocalCurrencyLiquidation(addres.notice: Calculates the net local currency required by the liquidator. This is a stateful method because it may settle the liquidated account if required. However, it can be called using staticcall off chain to determine the net local currency required before liquidating.

params.maxNTokenLiquidation: maximum amount of nTokens to purchase (if any)

returns._0: local currency required from liquidator (positive or negative)

liquidateCollateralCurrency(address,uint.notice: Liquidates an account between local and collateral currency

params.maxCollateralLiquidation: maximum amount of collateral (inclusive of cash and nTokens) to liquidate
params.maxNTokenLiquidation: maximum amount of nTokens to purchase (if any)
params.redeemToUnderlying: if true, converts collateral cash from asset cash to underlying
params.withdrawCollateral: if true, withdraws collateral cash back to msg.sender

returns._1: collateral asset cash paid to liquidator (positive)

liquidateLocalCurrency(address,uint16,ui.notice: Liquidates an account using local currency only

params.maxNTokenLiquidation: maximum amount of nTokens to purchase (if any)

returns._0: local currency required from liquidator (positive or negative)
